name: Look out
description: This Temtem has (metaphorical) eyes on the back of its head. This hyperalert state makes it alerted for 2 turns and removes the Asleep status condition.
effectText: Look out gifts the team with the Alerted Condition for 2 turns and cures them of the Asleep Condition. Unlike other techniques, it will set the duration of any previously gifted Alerted Conditions to 2 turns.

name: Lullaby
description: Twinkle twinkle little Tem / Whole opponent team falls Asleep for 2 turns.
effectText: Lullaby inflicts the rival team or the user's ally with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

name: Madness Buff
description: There is an edge to this madness - those willing to take 25% Damage will get SPDEF and SPATK.
effectText: Madness Buff causes the user to lose 25% of their maximum HP and then is gifted SPATK and SPDEF.

name: Magma Cannon
description: Like a surge of Anak lava to the face! Fire technique that burns for 2 turns.
effectText: Magma Cannon deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Burned Condition for 2 turns.

name: Major Slash
description: This blow targets the enemy's weak spot for massive damage.
effectText: Major Slash deals damage to a single other target.

name: Martial Strike
description: Many Melee Temtem are trained to perform this basic but effective technique.
effectText: Martial Strike deals damage to a single other target and grants the user SPATK.

name: Matter Teleport
description: Feels like being disintegrated into molecules - not nice. This Mental technique inflicts heavy damage.
effectText: Matter Teleport deals damage to a single target.

name: Mechanical Heat
description: Every moving part generates residual heat - and this is a way to weaponize it and inflict moderate damage.
effectText: Mechanical Heat deals damage to a single other target.

name: Meditation
description: Sync your breathing, become more aware of the space around you, feel your body and mind get Vigorized for 3 turns...
effectText: Meditation gifts the user with the Invigorated Condition for 3 turns.

name: Melee Stream
description: With strong muscles developed by swimming against the current, some Koish can do moderate Melee damage.
effectText: Melee Stream deals damage to a single target.

name: Melee Torrent
description: "Chromeon, show them your wrestling moves!" This technique inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Melee Torrent deals damage to a single other target.

name: Mental Stream
description: Related to ancient Cipanku river kami, this Koish has Mental powers that deliver moderate damage.
effectText: Mental Stream deals damage to a single target.

name: Mental Torrent
description: "Chromeon, mess with their heads!" This technique inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Mental Torrent deals damage to a single other target.

name: Metabolize
description: This metabolic enhancement reacts to poison in the target's body by purging it and recovers 20% of health.Used in combination with a Nature ally, improved assimilation of nutrients regenerates the Temtem for 2 turns.
effectText: Metabolize cures a single other target of the Poisoned Condition, restores 20% of the user's maximum HP and grants for 1 turn if the target was cured from the Poisoned Condition.
synergyText: If used with a Nature ally, it also gifts the user with the Regenerated Condition for 2 turns.

name: Meteor Swarm
description: Death from above... A barrage of flaming meteorites that inflicts Fire damage on the whole team.It's raining fire! Inflicts burns on the whole team.
effectText: Meteor Swarm deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.
synergyText: If used with a Fire ally, its damage increases to 90 and also inflicts the Burned Condition for 2 turns.

name: Mineral Hail
description: Imagine a Crystal storm in the darkest depths of Mictlan... Now just watch the enemy team.
effectText: Mineral Hail deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.

name: Mirror Shell
description: "Mirror, mirror in my hand, who's the best tamer in the Archipelago?" "No idea, but you get SPDEF".
effectText: Mirror Shell gifts the user with SPDEF.

name: Misogi

synergyEffects.effect:
3 Turns Immune
Removes negative Stat Stage Changes

description: The priests of Miyako developed this technique to eliminate all altered states and negative stages on the Temtem.Using this Waterfall meditation with a Water ally, the target becomes Immune for 3 turns and is freed from all stage modifications.
effectText: Misogi cures/removes all Status Conditions gifted/given/inflicted on the target and also removes the target's negative Stat Stage Changes.
synergyText: If used with a Water ally, it also gifts the target with the Immune Condition for 3 turns and all Stat Stage Changes are removed.

name: Mud Shower
description: Some of the larger Temtem of the savannah love this Earth technique, as messy as it is fun!
effectText: Mud Shower deals damage to a single target.

name: Multiple Pecks
description: A rapid-fire flurry of furious beaks.
effectText: Multiple Pecks deals damage to a single other target.

name: Nagaise's Fury
description: l, l! Nagaise is calling some Water friends from the deeps... The whole enemy team will regret this.Used in combination with a Mental ally, Nagaise's Fury inflicts extra damage.
effectText: Nagaise's Fury deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.
synergyText: If used with a Mental ally, its damage increases to 130.

name: Narcoleptic Hit
description: A potent attack that exhausts the attacker's psyche, making it fall Asleep for 2 turns.
effectText: Narcoleptic Hit deals damage to a single other target but inflicts the user with the Asleep Condition for 2 turns.

name: Nature Stream
description: Koish that live in dense brackish waters can channel the power of Nature to inflict moderate damage.
effectText: Nature Stream deals damage to a single target.

name: Nature Torrent
description: "Chromeon, hit them with the power of Nature!" This technique inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Nature Torrent deals damage to a single other target.

name: Neutral Stream
description: Cute but still fight-savvy, Koish know how to inflict moderate Neutral damage.
effectText: Neutral Stream deals damage to a single target.

name: Neutral Torrent
description: "Chromeon, shower them with torrential power!" This technique inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Neutral Torrent deals damage to a single other target.

name: Nibble
description: Many Temtem have this habit of gently chewing plants and furniture. This is a little less gentle.
effectText: Nibble deals damage to a single other target.

name: Soul Shout
description: A mighty scream, powered by the Temtem's very soul, inflicting considerable damage on an enemy.
effectText: Soul Shout deals damage to a single other target.

name: Sparkling Bullet
description: All flash and no bang - this sparkly Electric technique does little damage.
effectText: Sparkling Bullet deals damage to a single other target.
synergyText: If used with a Neutral ally, its damage increases to 105.

name: Sparks
description: Nothing perks you up like a spark-up! SPATK.
effectText: Sparks gifts a single target with SPATK and Invigorated Condition for 1 turn.

name: Strangle
description: Strangler and strangled, united in a deadly embrace. Both attacker and target get overextended next turn.
effectText: Strangle deals damage to a single other target but causes both the user and the target to be overexerted the next turn.

name: Swarm Aid

synergyEffects.effect: If above 50% HP targets lose 22% of maximum HP restore 17% of users maximum HP else targets lose 17% of maximum HP restore 22% of users maximum HP.

description: If HP is above 50%, allies restore 10% of max HP and rivals lose 15% of max HP. If HP is below 50%, allies restore 15% of max HP and rivals lose 10% of max HP.In combination with an Earth ally, if HP is above 50%, allies restore 17% of max HP and rivals lose 22% of max HP. If HP is below 50%, allies restore 22% of max HP and rivals lose 17% of max HP.
effectText: Swarm Aid causes the rival team to lose 15% of their maximum HP and restores 10% of the allies' maximum HP if the user is above 50% HP, else the target loses 10% of their maximum HP and restores 15% of the allies' maximum HP.
synergyText: If used with an Earth ally, its priority increases to Very High and instead causes the rival team to lose 22% of their maximum HP and restores 17% of the allies' maximum HP if the user is above 50% HP, else the target loses 17% of their maximum HP and restores 22% of the allies' maximum HP.

name: Tail Strike
description: Sweep the board at one fell swoop.
effectText: Tail Strike deals damage to a single other target.

name: Telekinetic Shrapnel
description: Reportedly feels "like combing your brain with concertina wire."
effectText: Telekinetic Shrapnel deals damage to a single other target.

name: Tenderness
description: Really? Are you going to attack something *this* cute? Inflicts ATK.
effectText: Tenderness inflicts a single other target with ATK.

name: Tentacle Whip
description: Tentacles. Why did it have to be tentacles?
effectText: Tentacle Whip deals damage to a single other target.

name: Tesla Prison
description: An electromagnetic trap that does light damage and slows down the target: SPD.
effectText: Tesla Prison deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with SPD.

name: Thunder Strike
description: Hear it roar! The sound and fury of this technique inflict heavy damage.
effectText: Thunder Strike deals damage to a single target.

name: Toughen
description: When the going gets tough, the tough get going - and DEF!
effectText: Toughen gifts the user with DEF.

name: Toxic Fang
description: A quick nibble that doesn't look like much... until you notice the Poison for 1 turn.
effectText: Toxic Fang deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Poisoned Condition for 1 turn.

name: Toxic Gas
description: Hold your nose when you unleash this Toxic attack on the whole team and inflict 1 turn of poison.
effectText: Toxic Gas deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally and inflicts the target(s) with 1 turn of Poisoned.

name: Toxic Ink
description: The victim will have time to regret getting this tattoo... While it's Poisoned for 2 turns.
effectText: Toxic Ink deals damage to a single other target and inflicts them with the Poisoned Condition for 2 turns.

name: Toxic Plume
description: Like a faulty airship engine, this Temtem can leave a trail of toxic gas that gives Poison to the whole team for 1 turn.Used in combination with a Crystal ally, Toxic Plume saves you STA and the target gets ATK.
effectText: Toxic Plume deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally and inflicts them with the Poisoned Condition for 1 turn.
synergyText: If used with a Crystal ally, its STA Cost decreases to 15 and also inflicts ATK.

name: Toxic Slime
description: This takes the form of a repulsive wave of slime that hurts the body, your self-esteem, and leaves lasting damage in the form of 1 turn of .
effectText: Toxic Slime deals damage to a single target and inflicts 1 turn of the Poisoned Status Condition.

name: Toxic Spores
description: Toxin-carrying spores that inoculate with Poisoned for 3 turns.
effectText: Toxic Spores inflicts a single other target with the Poisoned Condition for 3 turns.

name: Toxic Stream
description: Condensing waterborne toxins, Koish can use a stream of Toxic fluid that inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Toxic Stream deals damage to a single target.

name: Toxic Torrent
description: "Chromeon, show me your Toxic side!" This technique inflicts moderate damage.
effectText: Toxic Torrent deals damage to a single other target.

name: Toxin Shower
description: Soak everyone in nasty toxins - but don't splash yourself! Inflicts moderate damage on everyone but you, and lets you evade for 1 turn.
effectText: Toxin Shower deals damage to all other combatants on the battlefield and gifts the user with the Evading Condition for turn.

name: Trample
effectText: Trample inflicts damage to the rival team or the user's ally. If this technique knocks an opponent out, the user gets ATK and SPATK.
synergyText: If used with a Melee ally, it changes from a Special to a Physical technique.

name: Transient Echo
description: There and back again! This technique deals medium damage and gives -1 Hold.
effectText: Transient Echo deals damage to a single other target and gifts the user -1 Hold to all Techniques.

name: Tsunami
description: Summon a rarely seen tidal wave that damages a whole team.Uses in combination with a Wind ally, damage boost and Cold for 1 Turn.
effectText: Tsunami deals damage to the rival team or the user's ally.
synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, its damage increases to 80 and also inflicts the Cold Condition for 1 turn.

name: Turbine
description: Swift as the wind and as harsh and razor sharp as a wintery gale. This technique is fast and inflicts decent damage.
effectText: Turbine deals damage to a single other target.

name: Turbo Attack
description: Time to supercharge your attack - like nitro, but for Temtem!
effectText: Turbo Attack deals damage to a single target.

name: Turbo Charge
description: Turn it to eleven! Decreases the Hold level of our whole team.
effectText: Turbo Charge decreases the Hold of all the techniques of a single team by 1.

name: Turbo Choreography
description: The ancestral dance of Deniz is a powerful ritual that bestows protection, SPD to the whole team.Wind allies boost the effect of Turbo Choreography to the whole team SPD.
effectText: Turbo Choreography gifts a single team with SPD.
synergyText: If used with a Wind ally, it instead gifts SPD.
